uming symmetry properties of Cooper pairs (called\npairing symmetries), which can reduce candidates of pairing symmetries. We\nsubstantiate the power of our method through the time-reversal broken and\nnoncentrosymmetric superconductor CaPtAs. Our work establishes a unified theory\nfor understanding superconducting nodes and facilitates determining\nsuperconducting gaps in materials combined with experimental observations.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 15 Feb 2021 17:01:36 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 16 Feb 2021 16:01:18 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Tue, 24 Aug 2021 16:31:21 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-02-03"}
