ses $(X_t; t\\geq 0)$ are continuous on the\nintersection of suitable Besov spaces and any limit point $\\mu$ of the\n$\\mu_{M,N}$ is a stationary measure of $X$. $\\mu$ is shown to be a\nrotation-invariant and non-Gaussian probability measure and we provide results\non its support. It is also proven that $\\mu$ satisfies a further important\nproperty belonging to the family of axioms for Euclidean quantum fields, it is\nnamely reflection positive.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 16 Feb 2021 09:24:43 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 5 Apr 2021 23:36:17 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Fri, 15 Jul 2022 09:34:32 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-07-18"}
